<p class="">Two per cent. of the turnover. If the company makes motor cars, the 2 per cent. is on the motor cars. If the company makes motor cars and sells them at £500, its profit is £10 on that motor car—net profit.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
