            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-0f261e85-814a-427e-96d5-40e900a64183">
                Mr. Chamberlain
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-0f261e85-814a-427e-96d5-40e900a64183" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1949-11-03/debates/560d9054-37e5-4c45-a128-3defb98dfe05/ProfitsTaxBill#contribution-0f261e85-814a-427e-96d5-40e900a64183">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I apologise for again interrupting, but we ought to get this straight. Does the hon. Member not know that the limitation of dividends was a poor second best to what the Chancellor asked? Does he not remember that the Chancellor asked that industry should give a definite scheme for price and profit reduction, but that all he got was this "phoney" business of limitation of dividends?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-0f261e85-814a-427e-96d5-40e900a64183" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1949-11-03/debates/560d9054-37e5-4c45-a128-3defb98dfe05/ProfitsTaxBill#contribution-0f261e85-814a-427e-96d5-40e900a64183">
